<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-419-606  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 419 606.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 7 1990 v7 n18 p12(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>REXX support adds new power to OS/2. (IBM's REXX, a procedurallanguage; Mansfield Software Group Inc.'s Personal REXX)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schmidt, Denise.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Mansfield Software Group Inc. (products)International Business Machines Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   REXX (Communications software) (usage)Personal REXX (Compiler) (usage).andO;Topic:     CompilersCommunications software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>One of the more important additions in IBM's OS/2 Extended Edition (EE) 1.2is support for REXX, a powerful procedural language.andM;Although the REXX language was originally developed by IBM in the early 1980sand used under the mainframe VM operating system, this is IBM's firstPC-based incarnation.andM;Mansfield Software Group Inc. has offered Personal REXX for both DOS and OS/2for about a year.andM;IBM REXX, unlike Personal REXX, can interface with other OS/2 components,such as Presentation Manager, Dialog Manager and the Query Manager Interface.andM;According to Mansfield officials in Storrs, Conn., OS/2 interfacecapabilities will be included in the next release of Personal REXX.andM;IBM's REXX is not available for OS/2 Standard Edition or DOS.andM;Most sample programs included in the Personal REXX package were able to runwithout modification under IBM's REXX.andP;  However, Personal REXX is notentirely compatible with REXX -- each product includes features not found inthe other.andM;PC Week used modified sample programs from Personal REXX as benchmarks totest performance characteristics of IBM's REXX, including numericalcalculations, string handling, screen writes and file I/O.andM;Personal REXX outperformed IBM's REXX in these tests by 20 percent to 40percent.andP;  -- Denise Schmidt</TEXT></DOC>